{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Morning_at_the_Cafe",
  "title": "A Morning at the Cafe",
  "summary": "On a chilly morning in Commerce Square on Caspar, the wealthy Rodian arms dealer Gimel Daleth -- self-styled 'Hunter' and CEO of a weapons concern -- takes an outdoor cafe table with his ever-watchful bodyguard Sinter, drawing nervous bows from the locals. The CDU starfighter pilot Asli, on planet leave, is coaxed into joining him, and their wary banter about his wares is interrupted by the arrival of Asli's squadron commander Shadow, who knows Daleth from past arms deals and tails him with a recording astromech droid. When the clumsy newcomer Shintu spills hot caf on Asli, an alarmed Daleth -- recently the target of an assassination attempt -- pulls a hold-out blaster on him, only for the towering CDC officer Sh'par to intervene and defuse the standoff. Sh'par checks and confirms Daleth's extensive weapons permits, disarms the blaster's power pack as a warning, and lets everyone go their separate ways as the Horansi K'tyyri and her cubs look on. The crowd disperses, Daleth quietly instructing his arriving Quarren associate Krel to investigate Shadow's recording droid.",
